		<b>Comment By betty, 1-04-06</b>
		<p>I was born and raised in Louisville colo.  I moved to Wa. state in 1990.  Louisville is not what it used to be.  It used to be the way your friend had described it.  It was seriously like mayberry.  Everybody knew everybody literally.  You never did anything you didn't want your parents to know about, because they would find out.  We had 2 spag. resturants, Collachis and the plue parrot, and a hometown resturant, Karens country kitchen.  When i returned for my fathers funeral in 97 i was completely lost with all the new roads and construction, not the mayberry town i had left.  So sad. And homes were so much more expensive.  i dont know how anyone can afford to live in Louisville anymore.</p>
		
